{"name": "rag-eval-tool", "metadata": {"name": "rag-eval-tool", "version": "0.1.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["torch", "sacrebleu", "rouge-score", "bert-score", "transformers", "nltk", "textstat", "scikit-learn", "numpy", "protobuf", "tqdm"], "summary": "A comprehensive evaluation toolkit for RAG and LLMs.", "upload_time": 1735673459}, "documentation": ["# rag_eval_tool\r\n\r\nrag_eval_tool is a Python library designed for comprehensive evaluation of Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems and Large Language Models (LLMs). It offers a wide array of metrics to evaluate generated text across fluency, diversity, semantic similarity, readability, hallucination, and bias detection.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Features\r\n\r\n- **Text Similarity Metrics**: BLEU, ROUGE, BERTScore, METEOR, CHRF.\r\n- **Fluency and Coherence**: Perplexity using GPT-2.\r\n- **Lexical Metrics**: Diversity and Entropy.\r\n- **Readability Scores**: Flesch Reading Ease, Flesch-Kincaid Grade Level.\r\n- **Bias Detection**: Racial bias evaluation using a zero-shot classification model.\r\n- **Hallucination Metrics**: Quantify unsupported content in generated text.\r\n- **Precision/Recall/F1**: Measure token overlap between response and reference.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\nInstall the library directly from PyPI:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install rag_eval_tool\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "rag_eval_tool", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "rag_eval_tool.RAG_Eval_Tool", "xref": {"fqname": "rag_eval_tool.rag_eval_tool.RAG_Eval_Tool", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "rag_eval_tool.rag_eval_tool", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "rag_eval_tool.rag_eval_tool.RAG_Eval_Tool", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "rag_e